    <section class="go-hero">
        <h1>Gojri Alphabet Chart</h1>
        <p>The Gojri-English Alphabet Chart is a powerful cultural and ecological bridge designed for the children of the Gujjar and Bakarwal pastoral tribes in the Kashmir Himalayas. Gojri, their mother tongue, is rich with expressions reflecting their nomadic life and deep ecological knowledge. Since Gojri finds little space in formal schooling, this chart was created to affirm the child's identity and make learning relatable. This resource was created in collaboration with the Himalayan Pastoral Trust.</p>
